	(text "NOTE\n----\nIR UART Usually has IDLE (HIGH) being LED OFF, so 1 = OFF    0 = ON\nAnd the Receiver should reflect this:                 1 = OFF    0 = ON\n\nUse RECV and SEND for Normal Operation, and !RECV and !SEND for Inverted"
